            "created_at": "2010-08-23T21:38:19Z",
            "updated_at": "2010-08-23T21:38:19Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Browsers do not transmit mimetypes and guessing mimetypes from files is a huge security risk because of different algorithms for guessing mimetypes. This especially becomes an issue with different encodings as well. Never go down that road.\n\nThe only secure way to restrict uploaded files if they are served from a fileserver are file extensions because that's how a fileserver sets the outgoing content type. If you are emitting the content types (mimetypes) yourself you can use a filename independent system, but for which value?\n"
